Jenna Etheridge, News24Police Divers from Durban Search and Rescue along with Umhlali K9 SAR and IPSS Medical Rescue were called out to the Umgeni River in Kwadabeka below the New Bridge. (Supplied) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town &ndash; A 16-year-old boy who tried to cool off drowned in the Umgeni River in Kwadabeka on Friday afternoon, IPSS Medical Rescue said.The boy had apparently swum near the weir before getting into trouble, according to a statement by paramedics.Police divers recovered his body five metres under water.An inquest docket was opened. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.